ive;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">7</span></span></a> - WordPress plugin for calculating various farming and crop related information.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"climate-environment-and-weather\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#climate-environment-and-weather\" aria-label=\"climate environment and weather permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Climate, Environment and Weather</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/brycejohnston/agroclimatology\">agroclimatology</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/brycejohnston/agroclimatology\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a> - Ruby client for interacting with the NASA (POWER) Agroclimatology Web Resource.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ropensci/bomrang\">bomrang</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ropensci/bomrang\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">87</span></span></a> - Australian Government Bureau of Meteorology Data from R.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/brycejohnston/evapotranspiration\">evapotranspiration</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/brycejohnston/evapotranspiration\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a> - Ruby library for calculating reference crop evapotranspiration (ETo).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/waldoj/frostline\">frostline</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/waldoj/frostline\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">103</span></span></a> - A dataset, API, and python parser for USDA plant hardiness zones.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ropensci/GSODR\">GSODR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ropensci/GSODR\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">72</span></span></a> - Global summary daily weather data in R.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/akrherz/iem\">iem</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/akrherz/iem\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">88</span></span></a> - Code that makes the Iowa Environmental Mesonet run.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/woodcrafty/PyETo\">PyETo</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/woodcrafty/PyETo\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">85</span></span></a> - Python package for calculating reference/potential evapotranspiration (ETo).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hectornieto/pyTSEB\">pyTSEB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hectornieto/pyTSEB\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">68</span></span></a> - A python two source energy balance model for estimation of evapotranspiration with remote sensing data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ncss-tech/soilDB\">soilDB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ncss-tech/soilDB\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a> - R library for simplified access to NCSS soil databases.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"crop-modeling-phenotyping-and-pathology\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#crop-modeling-phenotyping-and-pathology\" aria-label=\"crop modeling phenotyping and pathology permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path 